WHO   — Ethics-Washing — the critique that companies use ethics boards and published principles as public relations while resisting binding regulation — the canonical case being Google's ATEAC advisory council, announced and dissolved within a week in 2019
WHAT  — the critique that companies use ethics boards and published principles as public relations while resisting binding regulation — the canonical case being Google's ATEAC advisory council, announced and dissolved within a week in 2019
WHERE — GOV · AI Ethics & Governance — David's charter + the global landscape (2016–2026)  Framework inputs: the Bill of Rights; the Governance Ontology; the principles; the cases; the instruments  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — It is the shadow over the whole field: the worry that 'AI ethics' becomes a brand applied from outside rather than a constraint felt from inside — which is exactly why the principle-practice gap matters.
HOW   — Crystallized from David's normative artifacts + the cited ethics-and-governance record.

